Image Downloader App
Overview
The Image Downloader App is a simple tool that allows users to specify a URL and automatically download all images from that webpage. This app is perfect for users who want to save all images from a particular website quickly and efficiently.

Features
URL Input: Users can input any valid URL from which they want to download images.
Automatic Image Detection: The app automatically detects all image formats (JPEG, PNG, GIF, etc.) on the specified URL.
Batch Download: All detected images are downloaded in a single batch to a specified directory on the user's device.
Progress Indicator: A visual indicator shows the download progress for each image.
Installation
To install and run the Image Downloader App, follow these steps:

Clone the Repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/image-downloader-app.git
Navigate to the App Directory:

bash
Copy code
cd image-downloader-app
Install Dependencies:

Ensure you have Python 3.x installed. Then, install the required dependencies:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the Application:

bash
Copy code
python app.py
Usage
Launch the App:

After running the application, a user interface will appear.

Enter the URL:

In the input field, specify the URL from which you want to download images.

Select Download Location:

Choose the folder where you want to save the downloaded images.

Start Downloading:

Click the "Download Images" button to start the downloading process. The app will display a progress bar indicating the download status.

View Downloaded Images:

Once the download is complete, navigate to the chosen folder to view the images.
